# Per-device SOPS secret files live here, one per cluster node.
#
# Naming: secrets/devices/<inventory_hostname>.yaml
#   e.g.  secrets/devices/vps1.yaml
#         secrets/devices/storage1.yaml
#
# Each file is encrypted for the operator keys AND for that node's own age
# public key (see .sops.yaml creation_rules).
#
# Required keys per file:
#   age-private-key    — the node's age PRIVATE key (AGE-SECRET-KEY-1...)
#                        written to /etc/age/<hostname>.key by nixos-anywhere
#                        (vps1) or /etc/hyphae/age.key by Ansible (other nodes)
#   netbird-setup-key  — one-time Netbird enrollment key from the mgmt server
#                        (not needed for vps1, which IS the mgmt server)
#
# vps1-specific additional keys:
#   netbird-store-key  — base64 AES-256 key for the management server SQLite store
#   coturn-password    — TURN user password for lt-cred-mech
#   coturn-turn-secret — HMAC secret for time-based TURN credentials
#   netbird-relay-secret — relay server auth secret
#
# To create a new device file:
#   1. age-keygen -o /tmp/<hostname>-age.key          # prints public key
#   2. Add public key to .sops.yaml (both cluster.yaml AND devices/<hostname>.yaml rules)
#   3. sops secrets/devices/<hostname>.yaml           # opens editor, fill in keys above
#   4. Commit the encrypted file; never commit the private key
